hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Yes, I play the guitar antiagingmedicine.com Following its horrendous mistake in underwriting the NHS bureaucracy – including its chief executive, David Nicholson, after Mid Staffs – the Government has now shifted. The Health Secretary, Jeremy Hunt, this week questioned Labour’s claim to NHS virtue, rather as Tony Blair once challenged Tory hegemony over crime. He is putting himself on the side of the suffering patient. He is promoting rigorous inspections, as in schools. This is the right way to go, but it comes very late.
